&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted by John D Taylor (CLC048)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I am retired and apart from still being a fellow of the Institute of Directors and having an interest in Amateur Radio I am not connected to, or funded by any other organisation or party.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Many years ago when the government of the day was proposing to drastically alter the way we live (wind farms c02 taxation and restrictions on the emissions of greenhouse gases) I decide to research the scientific basis for such dramatic action. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Unfortunately I was frustrated in this endeavour as it soon became obvious that there wasn’t any basis (there was no solid physical evidence to support manmade global warming) and that the voices the government was listening to was not that of dispassionate scientists but that of advocates with an agenda, either to raise funding for their pet projects, or from those with a quasi religious fervour to Save The World  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Now many years on the world’s population has increased by 50% and the7 billion of mankind is now consuming fossil fuels at an 
[normal]extraordinary
[normal] rate but Mother Nature has not responded to this massive influx of carbon. Temperatures have been flat for years and winter temperatures are now  falling  as  the  world  enters  a colder cycle
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Academics were wrong in 1970 to predict global cooling and they are wrong now to predict global warming,   with  new studies emerging on an almost daily basis, some with far reaching implications, it will be years before a better understanding of the climate emerges
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As an example
[normal]. 
[normal]The assumption has always been that more CO2 would increase temperature which would  cause more water vapour to raise the temperature further(positive feedback)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]About 5 years ago an East European Physicist  said this was wrong and that his mathematics indicate that water vapour would fall (negative feedback) and that Radio Sonde  Data backed this up. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Now Satellite data Release by NASA show that he was right  and water vapour falls with rising CO2.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]This means that   all the climate models are based on an incorrect assumption  and therefore everything we have been told by the Government and their Scientists is 
[normal](To put it mildly) badly flawed
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]There is also growing evidence that what we are seeing is not just s standstill in global temperature , but  the  start of a much colder period,. this view is supported by many, such as NASA, The Russians (K.Adbusamotov of the Pulkovo Observatory,
[normal] V Baschkin)&amp; R Galiulin of the Research Institute Vnigaz), Prof Don Easterbrook of Western Washington University and even the Met Office who admit that they cannot see any change before 2017
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I hope they are wrong I hope that someone somewhere in government is planning for the possibility of much colder weather because that really will be a disaster scenario not seen for a couple of hundred years 
[normal]FAMINE
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We can now see that there is no connection between CO2 and temperature, which reinforces the findings of the VOSTOK ice cores (that CO2 lags Temperature).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The temperature rise of the last hundred years has been 0.8 degrees Kelvin
[normal]This is a change of 0.3%. If the pressure in your car tyres changed by 0.3 % 
[normal]Would you get your knickers in a twist? I think not.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]So there is a problem with the scientific basis for Britain to reshape its economy and spend billions in taxes and subsidies to cut emissions of greenhouse gases
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]More CO2 means more food as hundreds of studies now confirm.
[normal]How lucky can mankind be when at a time of rapidly increasing population (8 billion by 2020) we have an increase in CO2 and thus food
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]10)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]All this of course leaves the politicians and their advisor’s in a dilemma
[normal]. 
[normal]They have spent many years and billions of doubloons going down an unjustified path
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]So what will they now do to convince a very suspicious electorate that is having problems with energy bills, that they know what they are talking about?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Also  we  have now got UKIP campaigning  that these policies are flawed so
[normal] I await the outcome with interest although I suspect I will have left this earth before this one is played out(damage limitation is the probable political response)
[normal]&#xa0;
